Increased cases of diseases with no available cure are ravaging rural communities. These include HIV-Aids, cancer and now there is the fear of the coronavirus pandemic. In Homa Bay County, Ikri Kendi is a welfare group that has gained popularity among rural communities. 

In Dholuo, Ikri Kendi literally means ‘bury yourself’. But what has driven villagers to come up with this bizarre idea that appears to focus on death rather than life? 

For one, increased cases of diseases with no available cure are ravaging rural communities. These include HIV-Aids, cancer and now there is the fear of the coronavirus pandemic. 



