So villagers in parts of Homa Bay have left these matters to divine intervention.  

Hopelessness has driven some villagers to ensure that should they be felled by these diseases, they can find solace in contributing money to plan for their burials, well in advance, just in case.  

This led to the formation of groups such as the Orinde Welfare Association (OWA), which is found in Kojwach Ward, that have attracted the membership of locals in large numbers.  



