Mr Oindi gave the following advice to members of the welfare groups during a meeting in Orinde Village: "I know it will be expensive for members but it will make a lot of sense to treat than to wait for death. It makes sense to preserve than bury life. 

"Our association has saved a lot of families from funeral-related squabbles with clanmembers because of lack of finances," said Mr Arara. 

A member of Kojwach Moyie said in an interview: "In this country, we are on our own. Even if we were to religiously pay for NHIF, there are diseases not covered and I will end up dying. Take for example Covid-19 and cancer, these diseases are everywhere and nobody is properly covered.  



